I'm this fragile, loopy--

479
00:45:30,374 --> 00:45:34,815
Well, I am seeing ghosts
in the bathtub, aren't I?

480
00:45:34,886 --> 00:45:38,268
You did wrap your car
around a tree, doing, like, 80.

481
00:45:38,342 --> 00:45:41,604
He was pretty shaken up.
We all were.

482
00:45:41,670 --> 00:45:46,853
It was an accident.
A year ago. I'm fine.

483
00:45:46,918 --> 00:45:49,373
Right?
[ Chuckles ]

484
00:45:49,446 --> 00:45:52,707
[ Sighs ]
Of course you are.

485
00:45:54,662 --> 00:45:57,978
You're just not much
of a medium, however.

486
00:45:58,054 --> 00:46:01,403
I'll call you tomorrow.
Get some rest.

487
00:46:01,478 --> 00:46:03,333
Did you pick up
any dudes yet?

488
00:46:03,398 --> 00:46:05,373
I have one in the trunk.

489
00:46:05,446 --> 00:46:09,505
[ Laughs ]
Bye.

490
00:46:09,574 --> 00:46:12,389
{y:i}[Car Drives Off]

491
00:48:03,014 --> 00:48:06,177
{y:i}- [Indistinct Voice]
- [ Gasps ]

492
00:48:30,789 --> 00:48:34,270
Wha-- What do you want?

493
00:48:34,341 --> 00:48:36,676
[ Panting ]

494
00:49:09,285 --> 00:49:11,587
- She's dead.
- Who's dead?

495
00:49:11,653 --> 00:49:14,784
- You know damn well who's dead.
- This is this Feur thing.

496
00:49:14,853 --> 00:49:17,919
Listen to me. He killed her,
and I'm not crazy!

497
00:49:17,989 --> 00:49:20,477
- Jody and I had a seance
in the bathroom--
{y:i}- Who did?

498
00:49:20,549 --> 00:49:25,251
Jody and I! Nothing happened.
But when I went back there,
she was there. She was.

499
00:49:25,317 --> 00:49:28,164
- [ Sobbing ]
{y:i}- Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

500
00:49:28,229 --> 00:49:30,367
{y:i}You-You had a seance?

501
00:49:32,612 --> 00:49:34,620
Are you angry with me?

502
00:49:34,693 --> 00:49:36,602
What?

503
00:49:36,677 --> 00:49:39,776
- Maybe you resent
how busy I've been.
- No.

504
00:49:39,845 --> 00:49:42,692
You know what I've got
at stake with this paper.

505
00:49:42,757 --> 00:49:45,179
- You know how important
this is to me.
- Yeah.

506
00:49:45,253 --> 00:49:48,187
I can't help but feel
that somehow you're
trying to sabotage me.

507
00:49:48,261 --> 00:49:51,108
- You're trying
to hurt me somehow.
- Norman, this isn't about you.

508
00:49:51,173 --> 00:49:54,555
Something is happening to me,
and it's not to get even or--

509
00:49:54,629 --> 00:49:57,476
and it's not some warped
bid for attention.

510
00:49:57,541 --> 00:50:01,851
Something is happening in our house,
whether you like it or not!

511
00:50:01,924 --> 00:50:03,932
[ Sniffling ]

512
00:50:04,005 --> 00:50:06,372
Claire.

513
00:50:06,437 --> 00:50:09,284
Claire, stop.
You're overreacting.

514
00:50:09,348 --> 00:50:11,388
Don't tell me how to react.

515
00:50:11,460 --> 00:50:14,177
- Will you keep your voice down?
- I will not!

516
00:50:14,244 --> 00:50:17,408
Maybe you're right.
Maybe I am losing my mind.

517
00:50:17,476 --> 00:50:20,738
But what if I'm not?
What if she died some--

518
00:50:20,805 --> 00:50:22,845
- Can we--
- some horrible death?

519
00:50:22,917 --> 00:50:25,121
Can we please not do this here?

520
00:50:25,189 --> 00:50:27,971
- Oh, wow.
- [ Indistinct Chattering ]

521
00:50:31,045 --> 00:50:36,260
You. You think
you're smart, don't you?
You think you got away with it.

522
00:50:36,324 --> 00:50:39,870
Well, I know you killed her,
you murdering son of a bitch!

523
00:50:39,941 --> 00:50:44,545
{y:i}- Who?
- Don't give me that shit.
Your wife!

524
00:50:44,612 --> 00:50:47,612
- [ Panting ]
- I'm sorry. She's very upset.

525
00:50:47,685 --> 00:50:50,500
- Forgive us, please.
- Honey.

526
00:50:50,565 --> 00:50:55,234
I didn't kill my wife.
Are you all right?

527
00:50:57,733 --> 00:51:00,766
[ Whispering ]
Come on, honey. Okay?

528
00:51:00,836 --> 00:51:05,375
- [ Pants ]
- Come on, baby.
Let's go. I'm sorry.

529
00:51:13,732 --> 00:51:15,642
- Hmm?
- Are you all right?

530
00:51:15,717 --> 00:51:18,815
Oh, yeah. I'm-I'm fine.

531
00:51:18,884 --> 00:51:21,153
What happened, just now?

532
00:51:21,220 --> 00:51:23,970
Oh, I-I just saw Norman's face.

533
00:51:25,636 --> 00:51:28,767
{y:i}Oh, he was
{y:i}so frightened for me.

534
00:51:28,836 --> 00:51:31,258
How's your marriage?

535
00:51:31,332 --> 00:51:33,536
Good. Really good.

536
00:51:33,604 --> 00:51:36,474
We've had our moments, I guess,

537
00:51:36,548 --> 00:51:40,442
but he's a wonderful
husband and father.

538
00:51:40,516 --> 00:51:44,477
I mean, sure, he can be
obsessed with his work,

539
00:51:44,548 --> 00:51:46,817
and sometimes it's like,

540
00:51:46,884 --> 00:51:51,008
um, that he doesn't see me.

541
00:51:51,076 --> 00:51:55,135
Or, you know, like I'm--

542
00:51:56,868 --> 00:52:01,657
that there's something
wrong... with me.

543
00:52:03,332 --> 00:52:05,241
That can't feel good.

544
00:52:05,316 --> 00:52:08,447
[ Chuckles ]
No.

545
00:52:14,564 --> 00:52:17,946
Okay, okay, I-I-I see where
you're going with this.

546
00:52:18,020 --> 00:52:20,988
But my marriage is fine.

547
00:52:21,059 --> 00:52:26,362
Now, I have had some kind
of empty nest episode...

548
00:52:26,436 --> 00:52:29,370
where I-I saw...

549
00:52:29,444 --> 00:52:32,259
some things
that weren't there.

550
00:52:33,636 --> 00:52:36,636
Let's deal with that.
I'm-I'm willing to deal with that.

551
00:52:36,708 --> 00:52:38,563
[ Sniffs ]

552
00:53:04,228 --> 00:53:06,911
"Thought you might need this.
Love, Jody."

553
00:53:06,980 --> 00:53:10,624
[ Chuckles ]
Uh-oh.

554
00:53:26,628 --> 00:53:29,116
Mrs. Spencer--

555
00:53:29,187 --> 00:53:32,089
[ Sighs ]
I wanted to apologize...

556
00:53:32,163 --> 00:53:34,268
for scaring you like I did.

557
00:53:34,339 --> 00:53:36,227
When I thought about what
that must have seemed like--

558
00:53:36,292 --> 00:53:40,962
Please, let-let's just--

559
00:53:41,028 --> 00:53:41,824
[ Sighs ]

560
00:53:41,892 --> 00:53:46,464
- Claire Spencer.
- Mary Feur.

561
00:53:46,532 --> 00:53:48,092
Would you like a cup of coffee?

562
00:53:48,164 --> 00:53:50,684
Very much.

563
00:53:50,755 --> 00:53:54,400
{y:i}That day at the fence,
{y:i}you seemed terrified.

564
00:53:54,468 --> 00:53:57,250
I-I don't think I imagined that.

565
00:53:57,315 --> 00:53:59,202
No.

566
00:53:59,268 --> 00:54:01,537
What were you so afraid of?

567
00:54:03,524 --> 00:54:07,997
Have you ever felt so completely
consumed by a feeling for someone,

568
00:54:08,068 --> 00:54:11,199
that you couldn't breathe?

569
00:54:11,267 --> 00:54:15,358
Thought that your time together
was so passionate and consuming...

570
00:54:15,427 --> 00:54:18,493
that you felt physical pain
when they would leave?

571
00:54:19,844 --> 00:54:22,015
Um, sure.

572
00:54:22,083 --> 00:54:25,378
I couldn't catch my breath,
and I panicked.

573
00:54:25,444 --> 00:54:28,258
I never dreamed
anyone would hear me.

574
00:54:30,019 --> 00:54:32,408
I tried to leave him.

575
00:54:32,483 --> 00:54:35,647
I went to my mother's
in Providence.

576
00:54:35,715 --> 00:54:40,766
But he brought my things up
in the middle of the night
during a rainstorm...

577
00:54:40,835 --> 00:54:43,453
and pleaded with me
to come home.

578
00:54:43,523 --> 00:54:46,305
- [ Sighs ]
- You must think that I'm pathetic.

579
00:54:46,372 --> 00:54:49,917
No. No. I, I don't.

580
00:54:49,987 --> 00:54:52,802
{y:i}I'll make this quick.
{y:i}I've just gotta talk to Sidon,

581
00:54:52,867 --> 00:54:55,834
get him to okay my budget
before he goes to Europe.

582
00:54:55,907 --> 00:54:58,428
What is Templeton's
wife's name again?

583
00:54:58,499 --> 00:55:01,182
- Lois, honey.
Phil and Lois Templeton.
- Lois, that's right.

584
00:55:01,251 --> 00:55:04,066
Don't let her corner you.
She'll chew your ear off.

585
00:55:04,131 --> 00:55:06,368
- Evening, Phil.
- There they are.

586
00:55:06,435 --> 00:55:08,289
- How do you do?
- Hi.

587
00:55:08,355 --> 00:55:10,395
- How nice to see you again, Lois.
- Hi.

588
00:55:10,467 --> 00:55:14,242
{y:i}- * [Classical]
- [ Chattering ]

589
00:55:29,859 --> 00:55:31,746
- Oh, hi.
- Hi.

590
00:55:31,811 --> 00:55:33,753
- Oh, stop it.
- [ Laughs ]

591
00:55:33,827 --> 00:55:36,248
Hi, Claire.

592
00:55:44,931 --> 00:55:47,517
[ Chattering Continues ]

593
00:55:59,395 --> 00:56:01,783
White wine, please.

594
00:56:05,539 --> 00:56:07,961
- Thank you.
- How are you holding up?

595
00:56:08,034 --> 00:56:11,101
- Just fine. It's a lovely party.
- Oh.

596
00:56:11,171 --> 00:56:14,170
Norman was telling me
the house is finally finished.

597
00:56:14,242 --> 00:56:16,414
- Almost.
- Wonderful.

598
00:56:16,483 --> 00:56:19,003
It's good to see you doing so well.

599
00:56:19,075 --> 00:56:22,239
- Thank you.
- Well, I was worried.

600
00:56:22,307 --> 00:56:26,617
I don't think I've seen you since
Norman's reception here last year.

601
00:56:26,691 --> 00:56:28,829
You were worried?

602
00:56:28,898 --> 00:56:31,484
I swear, I've become...

603
00:56:31,555 --> 00:56:34,370
that nosey old lady I used to run
away from at Amherst.

604
00:56:34,435 --> 00:56:37,282
No, no, I'm just
not sure what you mean.

605
00:56:37,346 --> 00:56:39,802
You, you got so upset.

606
00:56:41,155 --> 00:56:43,042
Oh, at the party.

607
00:56:43,106 --> 00:56:46,270
For the DuPont Chair.
You remember?

608
00:56:46,338 --> 00:56:49,121
Yeah, I remember
the party, but I--

609
00:56:51,426 --> 00:56:53,313
Oh, God.

610
00:56:54,691 --> 00:56:59,197
I had completely forgotten.
I, I broke your crystal.

611
00:56:59,266 --> 00:57:03,325
Oh, my dear.
Cheap wine glass from the caterers.

612
00:57:03,395 --> 00:57:05,784
But you went
completely pale.

613
00:57:05,859 --> 00:57:07,801
You couldn't get
your breath.

614
00:57:07,874 --> 00:57:10,144
It was as if you
had seen a ghost.

615
00:57:25,154 --> 00:57:27,707
{y:i}- [Glass Shatters]
- [ Gasps ]

616
00:57:41,346 --> 00:57:43,451
[ Gasps, Sighs ]

617
00:57:53,794 --> 00:57:56,096
"Missing girl."

618
00:57:58,466 --> 00:58:01,336
{y:i}"Madison Elizabeth."

619
00:58:03,298 --> 00:58:05,153
M.E.

620
00:58:17,666 --> 00:58:20,055
"Fank."

621
00:58:20,130 --> 00:58:24,254
{y:i}"Madison Elizabeth Fank."

622
00:58:26,114 --> 00:58:29,692
M.E.F.

623
00:59:04,513 --> 00:59:06,848
Claire?

624
00:59:08,001 --> 00:59:10,620
Hey, good morning.

625
00:59:13,986 --> 00:59:16,157
- You been up all night?
- Mm-hmm.

626
00:59:16,226 --> 00:59:18,201
You okay?

627
00:59:24,162 --> 00:59:26,650
Do you remember this?

628
00:59:30,081 --> 00:59:34,816
Uh, uh-huh. This is the girl
that disappeared last year.

629
00:59:37,250 --> 00:59:40,097
- Did you know her?
- No.

630
00:59:47,521 --> 00:59:49,910
Claire, I'm afraid to ask.

631
00:59:49,985 --> 00:59:52,887
[ Sighs ]
Where's all this going?

632
00:59:52,962 --> 00:59:55,101
It's her.

633
00:59:56,929 --> 00:59:59,929
{y:i}- The woman I saw in the bathtub.
- The ghost.

634
01:00:00,001 --> 01:00:03,776
{y:i}Yes, the ghost. I thought
{y:i}it was Mrs. Feur, but it's not.

635
01:00:03,841 --> 01:00:06,591
- Stop it, Claire.
Claire, stop it!
{y:i}- I'm positive this time.

636
01:00:06,657 --> 01:00:08,697
{y:i}Stop it!

637
01:00:11,361 --> 01:00:14,427
Look, I know you're
going through something
that I don't understand.

638
01:00:16,450 --> 01:00:20,028
And I have tried to be here
for you, but this is enough, Claire.

639
01:00:20,097 --> 01:00:21,984
Enough!

640
01:00:22,050 --> 01:00:24,766
Do you want to go
see somebody together?

641
01:00:24,834 --> 01:00:27,681
I'll call Dr. Drayton.

642
01:00:29,249 --> 01:00:31,638
Then what, Claire?
What?

643
01:00:31,714 --> 01:00:33,754
Tell me what to do.

644
01:00:33,826 --> 01:00:35,833
It's her.

645
01:00:38,049 --> 01:00:40,831
So let me ask you this,
Mr. McCain or--

646
01:00:40,897 --> 01:00:43,134
- McCann.
- McCann.

647
01:00:43,201 --> 01:00:47,936
- Uh, s-- nothing
was ever found, no car--
- No, nothing.

648
01:00:48,001 --> 01:00:51,711
Listen, uh, this girl's
a real live wire.

649
01:00:51,777 --> 01:00:55,606
She drives around in a souped-up
Mustang convertible.

650
01:00:55,681 --> 01:01:00,416
Most people around here think
she's off tooling around Mexico
somewhere with her fiends.

651
01:01:01,826 --> 01:01:05,022
Police downgraded it to a runaway.

652
01:01:05,089 --> 01:01:09,432
Um, her mother lives
out here in Addison County.

653
01:01:10,945 --> 01:01:14,011
- Mrs. Fank?
- Yeah.

654
01:01:14,081 --> 01:01:17,278
I'm Claire. Um--

655
01:01:17,345 --> 01:01:21,022
I wanted to talk to you
about Madison.

656
01:01:21,089 --> 01:01:25,791
{y:i}Just plain coffee.
{y:i}None of that mocha nonsense.

657
01:01:25,857 --> 01:01:28,126
{y:i}[Claire]
{y:i}Fine.

658
01:01:28,193 --> 01:01:31,455
You look a little old
for a student.

659
01:01:31,521 --> 01:01:34,718
Oh, I'm not a student.
Uh, we met at a party.

660
01:01:34,785 --> 01:01:38,232
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, well, that sounds about right.

661
01:01:38,305 --> 01:01:42,528
I never understood how
a girl that wild got all A's.

662
01:01:42,593 --> 01:01:44,698
She liked to read a lot, though.

663
01:01:44,769 --> 01:01:49,504
Sometimes she'd lock herself up
in her room for days, just reading.

664
01:01:49,569 --> 01:01:54,108
They wanted to put her in
a special school for the gifted
when she was young.

665
01:01:54,176 --> 01:01:57,592
[ Chuckles ]
Maddie wouldn't hear about it.

666
01:01:57,664 --> 01:02:01,210
I don't know where she got it.
She didn't get it from me.

667
01:02:02,593 --> 01:02:05,822
{y:i}She probably got it from
{y:i}her father's side of the family.

668
01:02:07,872 --> 01:02:10,141
She never really
mentioned her father.

669
01:02:11,553 --> 01:02:13,975
Yeah, well, she wouldn't.

670
01:02:14,049 --> 01:02:18,391
{y:i}She was 12 when he left.
{y:i}Never spoke about him after that.

671
01:02:18,465 --> 01:02:22,240
[ Sighs ]
You don't even need the sound.

672
01:02:24,225 --> 01:02:27,770
You can pretty much tell
what's happening by the faces.

673
01:02:29,217 --> 01:02:34,268
I turn it up sometimes, though.
Feels like there's someone here.

674
01:02:37,505 --> 01:02:39,479
Why are you here?

675
01:02:45,376 --> 01:02:47,580
I don't know.

676
01:02:47,648 --> 01:02:49,983
Do you want to see her room?

677
01:02:52,257 --> 01:02:54,712
{y:i}[Door Opens]

678
01:03:00,545 --> 01:03:03,806
Full scholarship. Princeton too.

679
01:03:05,376 --> 01:03:08,573
She wanted to stay
on the east coast.

680
01:03:08,641 --> 01:03:12,056
You must be so proud.
[ Chuckles ]

681
01:03:15,105 --> 01:03:18,007
These are the last pictures
taken of her.

682
01:03:18,081 --> 01:03:20,666
The police used this one.

683
01:03:20,736 --> 01:03:24,085
{y:i}- [Phone Ringing]
- Let me get that. Excuse me.

684
01:03:30,273 --> 01:03:32,760
{y:i}- [Mrs. Fank]
{y:i}- Hello?

685
01:03:32,832 --> 01:03:35,418
{y:i}[Continues, Indistinct]

686
01:04:38,400 --> 01:04:40,767
{y:i}[Door Opens]

687
01:04:40,832 --> 01:04:43,068
{y:i}[Norman]
{y:i}Claire?

688
01:04:43,136 --> 01:04:45,339
{y:i}[Door Closes]

689
01:05:04,064 --> 01:05:05,918
Claire?

690
01:05:10,720 --> 01:05:14,397
[ Smacks Lips, Sighs ]

691
01:05:20,864 --> 01:05:23,035
Hello, Dr. Spencer.

692
01:05:23,103 --> 01:05:26,933
Mrs. Spencer.
[ Chuckles ]

693
01:05:27,008 --> 01:05:28,862
Forbidden fruit.

694
01:05:31,808 --> 01:05:34,142
You got a problem with that?

695
01:06:25,055 --> 01:06:27,870
I guess this means you're
not mad at me anymore, huh?

696
01:06:27,935 --> 01:06:29,942
I wouldn't go that far.

697
01:06:32,895 --> 01:06:35,197
Oh.

698
01:06:36,768 --> 01:06:40,313
[ Laughing ]

699
01:06:42,816 --> 01:06:45,150
[ Sighs ]

700
01:07:12,575 --> 01:07:15,575
[ Grunts ]
Hey.

701
01:07:15,647 --> 01:07:18,167
Take it easy, huh?

702
01:07:23,839 --> 01:07:25,694
What's got into you?

703
01:07:28,671 --> 01:07:31,126
Mmm. Ow!

704
01:07:31,199 --> 01:07:34,014
- What's the matter?
- It's too rough.

705
01:07:34,079 --> 01:07:36,468
Since when?

706
01:07:36,543 --> 01:07:39,193
[ Grunts ]
You--

707
01:07:40,447 --> 01:07:44,473
- Jesus Christ,
it's a brand-new shirt.
- Shhh.

708
01:07:55,775 --> 01:07:59,387
- Claire, listen to me.
- Why don't you shut up, Professor?

709
01:08:00,927 --> 01:08:03,644
Why don't you just...

710
01:08:03,711 --> 01:08:07,573
shut up... and...

711
01:08:07,647 --> 01:08:10,963
[ Indistinct Whispering ]

712
01:09:19,903 --> 01:09:23,132
I think she's starting
to suspect something.

713
01:09:23,199 --> 01:09:25,054
{y:i}Who?

714
01:09:27,262 --> 01:09:29,302
- Your wife.
- [ Gasps ]

715
01:09:29,374 --> 01:09:31,862
Stop it!

716
01:09:31,935 --> 01:09:36,091
{y:i}[Gasps, Groaning]

717
01:09:43,582 --> 01:09:46,648
- You know.
- What the hell are you doing?

718
01:09:46,718 --> 01:09:50,428
I know.
[ Exhales ]

719
01:09:52,574 --> 01:09:54,429
I was there.

720
01:09:56,478 --> 01:10:01,464
Just before the accident.
Oh, I remember now.

721
01:10:01,534 --> 01:10:03,542
What?

722
01:10:03,615 --> 01:10:05,654
I came to the door.

723
01:10:05,726 --> 01:10:08,661
There was whispering.

724
01:10:08,734 --> 01:10:11,800
I saw you in the mirror...

725
01:10:14,238 --> 01:10:18,296
lying there... with her...
in our house.

726
01:10:18,366 --> 01:10:20,538
- Claire, listen to me.
- Oh, oh.

727
01:10:20,606 --> 01:10:23,508
She was at the DuPont party,
staring at me.

728
01:10:23,582 --> 01:10:25,437
- It was her.
- Honey.

729
01:10:25,502 --> 01:10:27,957
That's why I couldn't breathe.
That's why l--

730
01:10:28,030 --> 01:10:31,510
- That's why I dropped the glass.
- Honey, that was last year.

731
01:10:31,582 --> 01:10:34,484
- We were having troubles.
- So you slept
with a fucking student?

732
01:10:34,558 --> 01:10:36,697
- That's not what I'm saying.
- Don't touch me.

733
01:10:36,767 --> 01:10:39,133
Get away from me.

734
01:10:39,198 --> 01:10:42,459
[ Sobbing ]
Get out!

735
01:10:42,527 --> 01:10:45,309
I said get out!

736
01:10:46,814 --> 01:10:48,669
Fine.

737
01:10:48,734 --> 01:10:51,287
Claire, please, please--

738
01:10:51,358 --> 01:10:53,530
I gave up everything.

739
01:10:53,598 --> 01:10:55,605
Claire, please don't--

740
01:10:55,678 --> 01:10:59,126
- [ Sobbing] My life, my music!
- I never asked you to quit.

741
01:10:59,198 --> 01:11:01,467
Oh, there was never
any other choice!

742
01:11:01,534 --> 01:11:06,073
You had to-- to be perfect daddy.
That meant perfect wife,
perfect family!

743
01:11:06,142 --> 01:11:09,175
That's not fair.
You were a single mother
touring with a baby.

744
01:11:09,246 --> 01:11:13,753
You were happy to give it up.
And when you did, you hated me
so you gave it all to her!

745
01:11:13,822 --> 01:11:15,677
- Who?
- Caitlin!

746
01:11:15,742 --> 01:11:18,742
- You leave her out of this.
- And then, out of nowhere,

747
01:11:18,814 --> 01:11:21,334
- some bright young woman
finds me attractive--
- Stop it!

748
01:11:21,406 --> 01:11:24,984
- And I slipped.
God help me, I slipped.
- I'm not gonna listen.

749
01:11:25,054 --> 01:11:29,178
- Claire, I tried to break it off.
- You should've tried harder.

750
01:11:36,893 --> 01:11:38,901
I was in Adamant.

751
01:11:38,973 --> 01:11:41,145
In Adamant?

752
01:11:41,214 --> 01:11:45,785
{y:i}That artsy little hippie village
{y:i}a couple hours away down on 7.

753
01:11:45,854 --> 01:11:49,912
I stopped at this little cafe, and
I see Norman sitting in the back,

754
01:11:49,981 --> 01:11:52,283
but he wasn't alone.

755
01:11:52,350 --> 01:11:56,857
{y:i}It was a young blonde woman.
{y:i}I didn't see her face.

756
01:11:56,926 --> 01:11:59,544
And I didn't think
anything of it at first.

757
01:11:59,614 --> 01:12:02,363
I was walking over to say hello.

758
01:12:04,510 --> 01:12:08,121
And they started arguing
in such a way...

759
01:12:08,190 --> 01:12:10,840
that it stopped me.

760
01:12:12,221 --> 01:12:15,538
{y:i}And then a few days later,
{y:i}you were in the accident,

761
01:12:15,613 --> 01:12:19,159
{y:i}and I get a bizarre call from
{y:i}Stan working at the hospital,

762
01:12:19,230 --> 01:12:23,507
{y:i}asking me was I with you
{y:i}that day, if you were upset.

763
01:12:23,581 --> 01:12:28,185
{y:i}He made it sound like
{y:i}you had deliberately
{y:i}driven your car into a tree,

764
01:12:28,254 --> 01:12:33,523
{y:i}and I thought, "Oh, my God,
{y:i}Claire's found out. "

765
01:12:33,597 --> 01:12:36,281
{y:i}And when I went to the hospital,

766
01:12:36,350 --> 01:12:39,033
{y:i}I see Norman...

767
01:12:41,085 --> 01:12:44,151
and he was so desperate
at the thought...

768
01:12:47,037 --> 01:12:48,925
of losing you.

769
01:12:50,365 --> 01:12:52,787
{y:i}I couldn't say anything.

770
01:12:55,389 --> 01:12:57,244
{y:i}Please...

771
01:12:58,973 --> 01:13:01,461
don't hate me, Claire.

772
01:13:01,533 --> 01:13:03,988
I don't hate you.

773
01:13:05,918 --> 01:13:08,732
{y:i}[Phone Ringing]

774
01:13:08,798 --> 01:13:11,612
[ Answering Machine ]
Hello, this is Miss Jody.
Can't get to the phone.

775
01:13:11,678 --> 01:13:14,776
Leave your name and number,
and maybe I'll call you back.
[ Machine Beeps ]

776
01:13:14,845 --> 01:13:18,293
Jody, it's Norman.
I'm looking for Claire.

777
01:13:18,365 --> 01:13:22,588
Will you please--
Ask her to call home, please.

778
01:13:24,733 --> 01:13:27,002
{y:i}[Machine Beeps]

779
01:13:27,069 --> 01:13:29,622
I can't talk to him.

780
01:13:31,517 --> 01:13:35,030
Will you call him and tell him
I'll be home in the morning?

781
01:13:36,925 --> 01:13:39,194
I have to ask him something.

782
01:13:39,261 --> 01:13:40,893
{y:i}[Thunder Rumbling]

783
01:13:40,893 --> 01:13:42,453
{y:i}[Thunder Rumbling]

784
01:14:01,021 --> 01:14:02,930
Norman?

785
01:14:16,573 --> 01:14:19,955
{y:i}[Water Running]

786
01:14:31,965 --> 01:14:33,820
Norman?

787
01:14:36,733 --> 01:14:39,188
{y:i}Norman!

788
01:14:39,261 --> 01:14:42,130
No-- Oh, God.

789
01:14:42,205 --> 01:14:44,180
Norman!

790
01:14:44,252 --> 01:14:47,067
{y:i}- [Stan] How's his blood pressure?
{y:i}- [Woman] 140 over 80.

791
01:14:47,132 --> 01:14:50,449
{y:i}- And how about his rhythm?
{y:i}- Rhythm is normal. Normal sinus.

792
01:14:50,525 --> 01:14:52,696
- No sign of arrhythmia.
{y:i}- Good.

793
01:14:52,765 --> 01:14:55,580
Pulse ox is normal.
His pupils are equal and reactive.

794
01:14:55,645 --> 01:14:58,460
- I'd still like
to take you down, sir.
- I'm fine, really.

795
01:14:58,525 --> 01:15:01,874
- Dr. Powell, I'd recommend
a cardiac workup.
- Oh, please.

796
01:15:01,949 --> 01:15:05,877
- I'll take care of that.
- Okay, he just needs to sign
the release form, then.

797
01:15:05,949 --> 01:15:08,370
- Okay, thanks, guys.
{y:i}- Sure.

798
01:15:08,445 --> 01:15:12,220
Norman, they can take you
for a CAT scan tomorrow
if you start feeling dizzy.

799
01:15:12,285 --> 01:15:16,693
I'm not going to the hospital...
unless they have a miracle drug
for clumsiness.

800
01:15:16,765 --> 01:15:20,758
Honey, I'm so sorry.
I'm glad you came home.

801
01:15:20,828 --> 01:15:22,835
- Thank you.
- Oh, you're welcome.

802
01:15:22,908 --> 01:15:25,494
You know, if that breaker
hadn't popped, he--

803
01:15:25,565 --> 01:15:27,540
- I know.
- Yeah.

804
01:15:27,612 --> 01:15:31,387
Don't worry, Claire.
You just keep him quiet
tonight, okay?

805
01:15:31,452 --> 01:15:33,787
- Okay.
- Oh, in the future,

806
01:15:33,853 --> 01:15:37,562
you might want to think
twice about keeping anything
electrical next to the tub.

807
01:15:37,629 --> 01:15:39,865
- Oh, thank you.
[ Laughing ]
- Thank you.

808
01:15:39,932 --> 01:15:42,321
- Bye-bye. Call me, okay?
- Bye. Okay.

809
01:15:42,397 --> 01:15:44,666
- Oh.
- Bye-bye.

810
01:16:12,253 --> 01:16:16,857
I called you last night.
I left a message on Jody's machine.

811
01:16:18,492 --> 01:16:20,881
I want you to answer
one question.

812
01:16:23,356 --> 01:16:27,448
Did you have anything to do
with her disappearance?

813
01:16:29,116 --> 01:16:30,971
Yes.

814
01:16:34,364 --> 01:16:37,146
I had an affair with her.

815
01:16:38,524 --> 01:16:41,558
And when I tried to break it off,

816
01:16:41,628 --> 01:16:44,017
she became unstable.

817
01:16:46,204 --> 01:16:48,823
She came out here to the house.

818
01:16:50,140 --> 01:16:53,272
She threatened to kill herself...

819
01:16:54,908 --> 01:16:56,762
or you.

820
01:16:58,556 --> 01:17:02,484
I didn't think she'd
go through with any of it.

821
01:17:02,556 --> 01:17:06,036
But then she--

822
01:17:06,108 --> 01:17:08,312
she disappeared.

823
01:17:11,612 --> 01:17:14,711
It was her, Norman.
She tried to kill you.

824
01:17:14,780 --> 01:17:18,773
- Claire.
{y:i}- You said it yourself.
{y:i}She wanted you dead.

825
01:17:18,844 --> 01:17:22,193
Are you saying
I was attacked by a ghost?

826
01:17:22,268 --> 01:17:26,741
You had an affair with a girl
who threatened to kill herself,

827
01:17:26,812 --> 01:17:29,845
and now there's a presence
in our house

828
01:17:29,916 --> 01:17:33,397
a young, blonde girl.

829
01:17:33,468 --> 01:17:37,658
Don't you get it?
She did it, Norman.

830
01:17:37,724 --> 01:17:41,618
She's dead, and now
she's trying to hurt you...
or both of us.

831
01:17:41,691 --> 01:17:44,725
- We don't know that she's dead.
- Of course we do!

832
01:17:44,796 --> 01:17:48,091
It's the only thing
that makes sen--

833
01:17:49,820 --> 01:17:52,154
Oh, God.

834
01:17:52,220 --> 01:17:56,530
Oh, it's my-- it's my fault.
I-- I opened the door.

835
01:17:56,603 --> 01:17:58,643
- What are you talking about?
- Madison. I-I-I--

836
01:17:58,716 --> 01:18:01,171
- I stole a braid of her hair, and--
- from where?

837
01:18:01,244 --> 01:18:04,790
- And it gave her power.
- Claire, nothing attacked me.

838
01:18:04,860 --> 01:18:07,161
There are no ghosts.

839
01:18:07,228 --> 01:18:10,195
It was an accident. I'm fine.

840
01:18:10,268 --> 01:18:13,846
It's not your fault.
Are you listening to me?

841
01:18:13,916 --> 01:18:17,745
- Yes.
- Claire, say it. Say it.

842
01:18:17,819 --> 01:18:21,397
"It was an accident.
It's not my fault."

843
01:18:22,875 --> 01:18:25,014
Say it, Claire.

844
01:18:25,084 --> 01:18:27,735
I need to go lie down.

845
01:18:27,804 --> 01:18:31,382
I didn't sleep last night,
and I need to lie down.

846
01:18:33,595 --> 01:18:36,410
I want to be alone for a while.

847
01:18:55,579 --> 01:18:58,263
{y:i}[Norman]
{y:i}Hey, Teddy, it's me. Right, yeah.

848
01:18:58,332 --> 01:19:01,332
What's the name of that friend
of yours at Duke,

849
01:19:01,404 --> 01:19:05,233
the "who you gonna call" guy,
the guy that does the,
the paranormal psych stuff?

850
01:19:05,308 --> 01:19:07,609
- Holodnik.
- Holodnik, yeah.

851
01:19:07,676 --> 01:19:12,410
Um, could you contact him
and ask him to give me a call here?

852
01:19:12,476 --> 01:19:15,705
- I'd really, uh, like
to talk to him today.
- Sure, no problem.

853
01:20:20,571 --> 01:20:23,386
{y:i}[Phone Ringing]

854
01:20:23,451 --> 01:20:25,458
Hello?

855
01:20:25,531 --> 01:20:27,506
Yes, this is he.

856
01:20:27,579 --> 01:20:30,066
Thanks for calling back.

857
01:20:30,139 --> 01:20:34,646
Uh, no, sir.
That, that was my father.

858
01:20:37,307 --> 01:20:40,471
Yeah, he passed away
a couple of years ago.

859
01:20:40,539 --> 01:20:43,059
Yes, he was. Thank you.

860
01:20:43,130 --> 01:20:46,130
Look, the reason
I'm calling is I--

861
01:20:46,203 --> 01:20:49,302
I'm a little out of my depth
here, but, uh...

862
01:20:49,371 --> 01:20:53,462
someone who's very close to me,
um, uh, believes herself to be,

863
01:20:53,531 --> 01:20:57,874
or seems to be in, uh,
contact with some kind of...

864
01:20:57,947 --> 01:21:00,794
entity or spirit, and--

865
01:21:03,611 --> 01:21:08,117
No. No, there's no, um,
history of delusional behavior.

866
01:21:11,130 --> 01:21:13,399
But, well, I guess
what I'm asking is...

867
01:21:13,467 --> 01:21:16,052
is it possible that she could be...

868
01:21:16,123 --> 01:21:19,920
causing these manifestations
through some,

869
01:21:19,995 --> 01:21:23,573
some kind of unconscious
or telekinetic--

870
01:21:26,363 --> 01:21:29,178
Uh-huh.

871
01:21:29,243 --> 01:21:32,210
Well, is there anything else
that it could be?

872
01:21:36,155 --> 01:21:39,897
Uh-huh. And this
has been documented?

873
01:21:41,690 --> 01:21:44,178
Oh. Really?

874
01:21:46,394 --> 01:21:49,296
Um, listen, I'm sorry,
but could I ask you to--

875
01:21:49,370 --> 01:21:52,087
Can I call you back
or have you call me back?

876
01:21:52,154 --> 01:21:55,984
Please. Yes, that'd be great.
Thank you, sir.

877
01:21:59,034 --> 01:22:01,107
Claire!

878
01:22:08,698 --> 01:22:10,553
Claire!

879
01:22:34,810 --> 01:22:36,665
Claire!

880
01:22:54,874 --> 01:22:57,689
[ Gasps ]
God.

881
01:22:59,642 --> 01:23:02,359
- [ Coughing ]
- You all right, Claire?

882
01:23:02,427 --> 01:23:04,882
- The braid.
- What?

883
01:23:04,955 --> 01:23:07,256
The br--
Wh-Where's the braid?

884
01:23:07,322 --> 01:23:10,356
- What braid? What
are you talking about?
- [ Stammering, Coughing ]

885
01:23:10,426 --> 01:23:12,946
- Honey, what are you
talking about? This?
- [ Gasping ]

886
01:23:13,018 --> 01:23:15,407
- Is that what
you're talking about?
- Yes.

887
01:23:15,482 --> 01:23:18,962
- What is this?
Where'd you get this?
- I took it from Madison's house.

888
01:23:19,034 --> 01:23:22,383
[ Gasps, Coughs ]
This is hers?

889
01:23:22,458 --> 01:23:25,109
- This is Madison Fank's hair?
- Yes.

890
01:23:45,146 --> 01:23:47,513
What do you think?

891
01:23:47,578 --> 01:23:50,229
I really don't know.

892
01:23:53,914 --> 01:23:55,802
Norman.

893
01:24:00,410 --> 01:24:04,403
Yes... I believe you.

894
01:24:24,570 --> 01:24:26,610
Hey, Coop.

895
01:24:28,698 --> 01:24:31,283
{y:i}* [Cello]

896
01:24:45,786 --> 01:24:52,660
{y:i}*

897
01:24:52,729 --> 01:24:54,704
You're playing.

898
01:24:56,729 --> 01:24:58,584
She's gone.

899
01:25:00,154 --> 01:25:04,627
- How do you know?
- I can feel it.

900
01:25:12,537 --> 01:25:15,733
I picked up the book
you ordered at the bookstore.

901
01:25:23,994 --> 01:25:27,507
Claire, I don't know
how to apologize to you
for what I've done.

902
01:25:34,073 --> 01:25:38,328
But if you give me
another chance...

903
01:25:38,394 --> 01:25:42,485
I promise you I'll spend
the rest of my life making
you glad that you did.

904
01:25:55,513 --> 01:25:57,618
Please.

905
01:26:14,649 --> 01:26:17,366
Last sail of the year.
Beautiful, isn't it?

906
01:26:17,433 --> 01:26:21,426
- Mm-hmm.
- We oughta take a drive
before the leaves all disappear.

907
01:26:21,497 --> 01:26:25,556
- Stay at some little
bed and breakfast.
- Look for antiques.

908
01:26:25,625 --> 01:26:28,887
Yeah, we haven't
done that for a while.

909
01:26:28,953 --> 01:26:30,895
Adamant.

910
01:26:30,969 --> 01:26:32,856
Adamant?

911
01:26:32,921 --> 01:26:35,921
Yeah, an artsy
little village down 7.

912
01:26:35,993 --> 01:26:39,474
It's supposed to be charming.
Do you know it?

913
01:26:39,545 --> 01:26:41,454
No.

914
01:26:41,529 --> 01:26:44,562
Maybe we'll stop there for lunch.

915
01:27:03,673 --> 01:27:06,161
What's that for?

916
01:27:06,233 --> 01:27:08,087
Nothing.

917
01:27:19,129 --> 01:27:21,463
[ Moaning ]

918
01:27:28,345 --> 01:27:30,200
Hmm.

919
01:29:36,056 --> 01:29:38,642
[ Panting ]

920
01:29:44,152 --> 01:29:47,054
[ Gasps, Panting ]

921
01:29:49,688 --> 01:29:51,760
Oh, God.
Oh, God.

922
01:30:26,711 --> 01:30:30,573
You don't understand
what that is.

923
01:30:30,647 --> 01:30:35,382
Don't I, Norman?
It's Madison's... necklace.

924
01:30:37,783 --> 01:30:40,304
You killed her, didn't you?

925
01:30:40,376 --> 01:30:43,158
I did not.

926
01:30:43,224 --> 01:30:45,907
I didn't kill anyone.

927
01:30:47,831 --> 01:30:51,127
Jesus, Claire, listen to me.

928
01:30:52,631 --> 01:30:55,599
When I got here,
she was already dead.

929
01:30:55,671 --> 01:30:58,388
She killed herself here
in our house to destroy me.

930
01:30:58,455 --> 01:31:00,725
Do you think
that I'm stupid?

931
01:31:00,792 --> 01:31:03,956
She left that for you
in the garden with a letter.

932
01:31:04,024 --> 01:31:06,958
I burned the letter,
and I threw the box in the lake.

933
01:31:07,031 --> 01:31:09,398
A week before...

934
01:31:09,463 --> 01:31:13,009
sh-she showed up
at the DuPont party.

935
01:31:15,991 --> 01:31:18,326
I was terrified.

936
01:31:18,392 --> 01:31:21,294
She insisted,
so I agreed to meet her here.

937
01:31:21,368 --> 01:31:25,077
When I got here,
she'd taken pills.

938
01:31:25,144 --> 01:31:30,446
I, I tried to revive her,
but... she was gone.

939
01:31:30,520 --> 01:31:33,684
There was nothing
I could do.

940
01:31:33,752 --> 01:31:38,324
So-- So I put her
in her car, and l--

941
01:31:38,392 --> 01:31:41,261
I drove
to the boat ramp...

942
01:31:41,335 --> 01:31:44,084
and I rolled it
out into the lake.

943
01:31:44,152 --> 01:31:47,534
{y:i}I made a terrible mistake.
{y:i}I know that.

944
01:31:47,607 --> 01:31:50,902
But tell me, Claire, tell me,
what should I have done?

945
01:31:50,967 --> 01:31:54,928
Should I sacrifice everything?
Our marriage?

946
01:31:54,999 --> 01:31:59,025
My work, which I've
spent my whole life on?

947
01:32:00,791 --> 01:32:04,239
Tell me, Claire.
Tell me, please.

948
01:32:04,312 --> 01:32:07,126
'Cause we can
put this behind us.

949
01:32:07,191 --> 01:32:10,574
Our life can go on.
It's not too late.

950
01:32:13,847 --> 01:32:16,116
What are you asking me to do?

951
01:32:18,167 --> 01:32:20,752
